<h2>About v11.0.0 Update</h2>

<!-- update-description-begin -->

<div class="update-description">

  <div class="update-description-item update-description-item-new">
    <div class="update-description-label"></div>
    <div class="update-description-body">
      v11.0.0:<br />
      <ul>
        <li>
          The first stable release of Karabiner-Elements.<br />
          (There is no changes from Karabiner-Elements 0.91.16.)
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="update-description-item update-description-item-new">
    <div class="update-description-label"></div>
    <div class="update-description-body">
      v0.91.16:<br />
      <ul>
        <li>Karabiner-Elements waits grabbing device until all modifier keys are released in order to avoid modifier flags stuck issue in mouse events.</li>
        <li>Support consumer keys (e.g., media key events in Logitech keyboards.)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="update-description-item update-description-item-new">
    <div class="update-description-label"></div>
    <div class="update-description-body">
      v0.91.13:<br />
      <ul>
        <li>
          Add per device support in `Simple Modifications` and `Fn Function Keys`. <br />
          <img src="https://pqrs.org/osx/karabiner/img/news/v0.91.13_0.png" alt="Simple Modifications" class="img" />
        </li>
        <li>The modifier flag event handling has been improved.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- update-description-end -->
<p>
  <a href="https://pqrs.org/osx/karabiner/history.html">More</a>
</p>
